1. Appropriate Personal Protective Equipment (PPE), as outlined in SDS sheets, including but not limited to, any cleaning of restrooms;
2. Floor mats, if needed, where they do not compromise safety and or the ability to clean and sanitize;
3. Fall protection equipment and other appropriate health and safety devices when required by OSHA rules.

